the java Arrays class: 
http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Arrays.html
It's very handy class to help for array.
1. Arrays.sort(array) : sort the array
2. Arrays.copyOf(array, int newLength) : copy an array to a new array
3. Arrays.equals(array1, array2) : compare each element of two arrays.
4. Arrays.fill(array, value), fill the whole array of a given value. the type of value must be the same as type of array
5. Arrays.toString(array), very useful when writing printing method. It returns an string representation of the array contents